cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.AI 

This paper is primarily focused on the analysis of Graph Convolutional Neural Networks (graph CNNs) and their expressive power. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses dynamical systems theory to analyze the behavior of graph CNNs, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper discusses the topological information of graphs, which could place it under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes a weight normalization technique for graph CNNs, which could also classify it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
